==Game notes== ===South Carolina=== Gambino scored three touchdowns and Maryland firmly held the momentum for the first three quarters. In the final period, South Carolina mounted a comeback attempt. Maryland player Gene Kinney intercepted a pass on the Terrapin 31-yard line to secure the victory, 19â13.<ref>''Terrapin'', University of Maryland yearbook, Class of 1948, p. 240.</ref>
===Delaware=== Delaware entered the game atop a 32-game winning streak. Gambino again scored three touchdowns, with others added by Davis, Idzik, and Targarona. The Blue Hens responded to an 88-yard touchdown run by Gambino with a 90-yard score by Cole.<ref>''Terrapin'', University of Maryland yearbook, Class of 1948, p. 241.</ref>
=== Richmond=== Maryland avenged the previous season's loss to Richmond. Gambino scored twice and completed a pass to Simler for the third touchdown.<ref>''Terrapin'', University of Maryland yearbook, Class of 1948, p. 242.</ref>
=== Duke (#17)=== Maryland fumbles and interceptions helped Duke snap the three-game winning streak. Vernon Seibert scored the Terrapins' only score of the day. It was also the first touchdown ever scored by Maryland against Duke.<ref>''Terrapin'', University of Maryland yearbook, Class of 1948, p. 243.</ref>
=== Virginia Tech=== Virginia Tech scored twice in the first quarter after Maryland penalties and a turnover. In the fourth quarter, Maryland mounted a two-touchdown rally to spoil Virginia Tech's homecoming, 21â19. The decisive scores were due to a long Vic Turyn pass to Simler and a 32-yard dash by Idzik. McHugh made all three point after touchdown kicks, which proved to be the margin of victory.<ref>''Terrapin'', University of Maryland yearbook, Class of 1948, p. 244.</ref>
